org.snakeskin.component.provider

Interface IPercentOutputMotorControlProvider

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    IDirectMotorControllerBasicComponent, IMotorControllerBasic, IMotorControllerSmart, INetworkMotorControllerEnhancedComponent, INetworkMotorControllerSmartComponent
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    SoftwareDirectMotorControllerBasicComponent, SoftwareNetworkMotorControllerEnhancedComponent, SoftwareNetworkMotorControllerSmartComponent

    public IPercentOutputMotorControlProvider

    Represents a component that provides basic percent output control

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Default Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      double getInputVoltage()
      Returns the input voltage to this component. Depending on the implementation, this could be reading from the PDP VBus
      double getOutputVoltage()
      Returns the output voltage from this component. Depending on the implementation, this could be using the PDP VBus to approximate the output voltage
      double getPercentOutput()
      Returns the percent output that this component is currently applying
      void setPercentOutput(double percentOut)
      Sets the percent output of this component to the specified value
      void stop()
      Sets the percent output of this component to zero. Depending on the configuration of the motor controller, this could cause it to either coast or brake to a stop.
